   <text>
      <body>
         <head>Sample 01: tagsets in taxonomies</head>
         <p>This document demonstrates setting up tagsets by using the mechanism of taxonomy declarations in the TEI header.</p>
         <p>One immediate consequence that can be noticed is that feature values must receive
            compound values, the first part of which acts as the namespace, hence "STTS" or "UD",
            etc. as the prefix.</p>
         <p>Another important consequence is that, since feature values are set up as IDs, they have
            to obey XML restrictions on IDs, and in particular, they may not contain commas or
            brackets -- compare the last symbols for punctuation in STTS, where I needed to use the
            full names ("sttsInternalPunctuation" instead of "$("). Farewell short tags...</p>
         <p>As far as the category level of tagset definition is concerned, it offers only limited
            documentation options, basically via <gi>desc</gi> . <gi>catDesc</gi> is not allowed if
            the <gi>equiv</gi> elements are to be used. Note by the way that adding <gi>catDesc</gi>
            to the <ident type="class">att.datcat</ident> class, and then it could use the
               <att>datcat</att> attribute (an issue debated for this class of elements back in 2012).</p>
      </body>
